The paper discusses programming with replicated objects, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC). It also mentions two popular storage systems, Cassandra and ZooKeeper, which are commonly used in distributed databases (cs.DB) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper proposes a new abstraction for handling consistency and performance trade-offs, which is a topic related to software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL).
